## print a authors of this repo

    peter@peter-laptop:~/gitbro$ git log --format='%aN <%aE>' | awk
    '{arr[$0]++} END{for (i in arr){print arr[i], i;}}' | sort -rn | cut -d\  -f2-

    
    git log --format='%aN' | sort -u
    git shortlog -s|cut -c8-


## website
luckily I find: we still have our branch `website`
`git br` can not show it, but `tig --all` will.
and we can actually use 

	git check -b website <the_latest_commit_on_branch_website>

to get it back

